Beliefs and behaviors related to COVID-19 in two Nigerian states

A survey in Edo and Delta

We are currently conducting phone surveys on a previously constructed sample of individuals in Edo and Delta states in Nigeria to address research and policy questions related to COVID-19. The aim of the survey is to contribute insights about existing coronavirus-related health beliefs and behaviors, such as the spatial distribution of disease awareness, socio-economic and other correlates of awareness, and compliance with government issued guidelines on social distancing and hand-washing. Our COVID-19 module also provides information about how to keep oneself and others healthy and safe.1

Definitions of measures

Data definitions
Measure Definition Range Respone options
Experiencing fever Are you currently experiencing any of the following symptoms? Fever 0 - 1 1=Yes; 0=No
Experiencing cough Are you currently experiencing any of the following symptoms? Cough 0 - 1 1=Yes; 0=No
Experiencing difficulty breathing Are you currently experiencing any of the following symptoms? Difficulty breathing / shortness of breath 0 - 1 1=Yes; 0=No
Experiencing headache Are you currently experiencing any of the following symptoms? Headache 0 - 1 1=Yes; 0=No
Experiencing muscle pain Are you currently experiencing any of the following symptoms? Muscle pain / body aches 0 - 1 1=Yes; 0=No
Household with symptoms Does someone in your household currently have ANY of the following symptoms? 0 - 1 1=Any symptom; 0=No symptom
# of people in hh with symptoms How many people in your household are experiencing these symptoms? 0 - 1 1=At least one; 0=No one

Definitions of measures

Data definitions
Measure Definition Range Respone options
Likelihood of infection in NGA How likely do you think it is that someone like you will be infected with the new coronavirus in NIGERIA? 1 - 6 1=Extremely unlikely; 6=Extremely likely
Likelihood of death in NGA If someone like you was infected with the new coronavirus in NIGERIA, how likely do you think it is that they would pass? 1 - 6 1=Extremely unlikely; 6=Extremely likely
More likely to die from Covid than Malaria? And how likely do you think it is that they would pass away from an infection with the new coronavirus, relative to the risk of passing away while being sick with malaria? 1 - 5 1=Much less likely; 5=Much more likely
Likelihood of infection in Europe And how likely do you think it is that someone like you would be infected with the new coronavirus in EUROPE? 1 - 6 1=Extremely unlikely; 6=Extremely likely
Likelihood of death in Europe If someone like you was infected with the new coronavirus in EUROPE, how likely do you think it is that they would pass? 1 - 6 1=Extremely unlikely; 6=Extremely likely
More likely to get Covid in NGA than Europe? In your view, is someone like you MORE likely OR LESS likely to be infected with the new coronavirus IN NIGERIA COMPARED TO someone like you in EUROPE? 1 - 5 1=Much less likely; 5=Much more likely
More likely to die from Covid in NGA than Europe? And if infected, is someone like you MORE likely to pass away IN NIGERIA COMPARED TO EUROPE, or LESS likely? 1 - 5 1=Much less likely; 5=Much more likely
Likelihood that self would get Covid How likely do you think it is that YOU will be infected with the new coronavirus? 1 - 6 1=Extremely unlikely; 6=Extremely likely
Likelihood of self dying from Covid Again, thinking about you personally: If YOU were infected with the new coronavirus, how likely do you think it is that you would pass? 1 - 6 1=Extremely unlikely; 6=Extremely likely

Distribution of standardized variables

Definitions of measures

Data definitions
Measure Definition Range Respone options
Stayed home last week To what extent does the following statement describe your behavior during the past week (seven days)? I stayed at home 1 - 4 1=I did not do this; 4=All of the time
Avoided gatherings last week To what extent does the following statement describe your behavior during the past week (seven days)? I stayed away from social gatherings 1 - 4 1=I did not do this; 4=All of the time
Kept 2m distance last week To what extent does the following statement describe your behavior during the past week (seven days)? I kept a distance of at least two meters to other people not from my household. 1 - 4 1=I did not do this; 4=All of the time
Washed hands more last week To what extent does the following statement describe your behavior during the past week (seven days)? I washed my hands with soap and water more frequently than at the beginning of the year 1 - 4 1=I did not do this; 4=All of the time
Weared a mask last week To what extent does the following statement describe your behavior during the past week (seven days)? I wore a mask 1 - 4 1=I did not do this; 4=All of the time
Would inform others if get Covid How much do you agree with the following statement: “If I had shown symptoms of sickness, I would have immediately told the people around me.” 1 - 5 1=Strongly disagree; 5=Strongly agree
Attended prayers last week In the past seven days, how many days did you attend church or mosque, or gathered with people from outside your household to pray? 0 - 1 1=At least one day; 0=Never

Definitions of measures

Data definitions
Measure Definition Range Respone options
How appropiate is gov response Do you think the reaction of the Nigerian federal government to the current coronavirus outbreak is appropriate, goes too far, or does not go far enough? 1 - 5 1=Does not go nearly far enough; 5=Goes much too far
Gov information is truthful How factually truthful do you think the Nigerian federal government has been about the coronavirus outbreak? 1 - 5 1=Very untruthful; 5=Very truthful
Trust in the NCDC How much do you trust the following sources of information on the coronavirus: Nigeria CDC (Nigeria Center for Disease Control) 1 - 5 1=Strongly distrust; 5= Strongly trust
Trust the WHO How much do you trust the following sources of information on the coronavirus: World Health Organization (WHO) 1 - 5 1=Strongly distrust; 5= Strongly trust
Trust the news How much do you trust the following sources of information on the coronavirus: News media (print, TV, radio) 1 - 5 1=Strongly distrust; 5= Strongly trust
